WEBVTT

00:00.345 --> 00:02.169
MM. NOW, THAT'S HOW YOU
MAKE A POT OF COFFEE.

00:02.169 --> 00:03.769
I DON'T KNOW HOW I FEEL
ABOUT MY HUSBAND

00:03.769 --> 00:05.639
SPENDING A NIGHT ON THE ROAD
WITH HIS FIRST EX-WIFE,

00:05.639 --> 00:07.641
ADJOINING HOTEL ROOMS...

00:07.641 --> 00:10.010
SUDDENLY, IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT,

00:10.010 --> 00:11.144
THE DOOR CRACKS OPEN.

00:11.144 --> 00:13.247
STOP. YOU KNOW
I HATE SCARY STORIES.

00:13.247 --> 00:14.982
DIANE IS STANDING THERE

00:14.982 --> 00:17.651
IN HER STIFF, MONOGRAMMED
COTTON PAJAMAS,

00:17.651 --> 00:19.620
TELLING YOU THAT YOU'RE
BRUSHING YOUR TEETH WRONG.

00:19.620 --> 00:20.487
[ CAR HORN HONKS ]

00:20.487 --> 00:21.989
HOW IS HILLARY
SO EXCITED

00:21.989 --> 00:23.757
TO SPEND HER SPRING BREAK
AT SCIENCE CAMP

00:23.757 --> 00:25.993
THAT SHE'S BEEN SITTING
IN THE CAR FOR THE PAST HOUR?

00:25.993 --> 00:27.561
THAT'S JUST THE HOUR
WE KNOW ABOUT.

00:27.561 --> 00:29.196
I HADN'T SEEN HER
SINCE LAST NIGHT.

00:30.030 --> 00:31.265
HEY, BUD.

00:33.066 --> 00:34.268
OH, KATE,
THE LAMP FELL.

00:34.268 --> 00:35.736
BUD, WHY ARE YOU BRINGING
SO MANY CLOTHES?

00:35.736 --> 00:38.338
WE'RE JUST GONNA DROP HILLARY
OFF, COME RIGHT BACK TOMORROW.

00:38.338 --> 00:40.107
HOW MANY PAIRS OF SOCKS
DO YOU NEED?

00:40.107 --> 00:41.108
SOCKS!

00:41.108 --> 00:42.576
OH, HEY, WARREN.

00:42.576 --> 00:44.611
KATE, THE LAMP FELL.

00:44.611 --> 00:46.980
SO, DIANE, ARE YOU NERVOUS
ABOUT HILLARY GOING AWAY

00:46.980 --> 00:48.682
FOR THE FIRST TIME?

00:48.682 --> 00:51.685
[ LAUGHS ] NOT AT ALL.
SHE'S INCREDIBLY INDEPENDENT.

00:51.685 --> 00:53.720
SHE WAS POTTY-TRAINED
AT EIGHT MONTHS. [ SNIFFS ]

00:53.720 --> 00:57.457
[ COFFEE POURING ]
I THINK SHE CAN HANDLE ONE WEEK
ON A COLLEGE CAMPUS.

00:57.457 --> 00:59.059
YOU SHOULD COME ALONG,
KATE.

00:59.059 --> 01:03.096
IT WOULD BE YOUR OPPORTUNITY
TO FINALLY SEE ONE IN REAL LIFE.

01:03.096 --> 01:04.264
WELL, I WENT TO COLLEGE,
DIANE, OKAY?

01:04.264 --> 01:05.399
I HAVE A DEGREE.

01:05.399 --> 01:07.167
I JUST DON'T ANNOUNCE IT
EVERY TWO MINUTES.

01:07.167 --> 01:08.235
WELL, NEITHER DO I.

01:08.235 --> 01:10.070
IF THERE'S ONE THING
STANFORD TAUGHT ME,

01:10.070 --> 01:11.271
IT'S THAT STANFORD GRADS

01:11.271 --> 01:13.674
ALWAYS HAVE THAT FAMOUS
STANFORD HUMILITY.

01:14.708 --> 01:16.677
OH, YOU CAN ROLL YOUR EYES
ALL YOU WANT, KATE,

01:16.677 --> 01:18.245
BUT I AM NOT SHOWING OFF.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.080
I'M JUST STATING A FACT.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.415
AND IF I WERE
SHOWING OFF,

01:21.415 --> 01:23.417
I WOULD TELL YOU THAT I WOKE UP
AT 4:15 THIS MORNING

01:23.417 --> 01:26.753
TO REATTACH A FLOATING PATELLA
WITH A CADAVER LIGAMENT

01:26.753 --> 01:28.121
TO AN OBESE MAN.

01:28.121 --> 01:30.357
OBESE KNEES
ARE THE HARDEST.

01:30.357 --> 01:32.059
OKAY,
MY CAR IS ALL PACKED.

01:32.059 --> 01:33.193
YOUR CAR?

01:33.193 --> 01:34.428
YEAH,
I THOUGHT I'D DRIVE.

01:34.428 --> 01:36.229
YOU THOUGHT WRONG.
I'M DRIVING.

01:36.229 --> 01:37.364
OH, AND, PETER,

01:37.364 --> 01:39.166
I CAN TELL
YOU HAVE TO POTTY,

01:39.166 --> 01:42.235
SO YOU MIGHT LIKE TO DO SO NOW
BECAUSE I'M NOT STOPPING.

01:42.235 --> 01:43.136
SAVE ME.

01:43.136 --> 01:45.172
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN,
BUDDY.

01:48.041 --> 01:57.517
♪♪♪

02:02.255 --> 02:03.724
OH, YEAH.

02:06.727 --> 02:07.728
AHH!

02:07.728 --> 02:08.762
AHH.

02:08.762 --> 02:10.097
AAH!
YEAH.

02:10.097 --> 02:12.099
JACKIE, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN HERE?

02:12.099 --> 02:14.301
LONG ENOUGH
TO TAKE OFF MY BRA, TOO.

02:14.301 --> 02:15.469
JUST KIDDING.

02:15.469 --> 02:18.105
I NEVER WEAR A BRA.
[ GRUNTS ]

02:18.105 --> 02:20.107
HEY, YOU KNOW
I NEVER ASK FOR HELP...

02:20.107 --> 02:22.075
YOU ALWAYS
ASK FOR HELP.

02:22.075 --> 02:24.311
...WHICH IS HOW YOU KNOW
THAT THIS IS REAL IMPORTANT.

02:24.311 --> 02:27.114
I'M SUPPOSED TO GO TO
MY HIGH-SCHOOL REUNION
TONIGHT WITH SAD STEVE,

02:27.114 --> 02:30.050
BUT HIS MOM
FELL INTO A REALLY DEEP COMA,

02:30.050 --> 02:32.119
WHICH IS SUPER-TRAGIC,
OBVIOUSLY,

02:32.119 --> 02:35.055
BECAUSE NOW
I DON'T HAVE A DATE.

02:35.055 --> 02:36.456
OOH, DON'T YOU HATE IT
HOW SOME PEOPLE

02:36.456 --> 02:38.659
JUST MAKE EVERYTHING
ABOUT THEMSELVES?

02:38.659 --> 02:40.127
OH, I KNOW!
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

02:40.127 --> 02:42.195
IT'S, LIKE, I DON'T HAVE ANYONE
TO GO WITH IT,

02:42.195 --> 02:43.764
AND I CAN'T GO BY MYSELF.

02:43.764 --> 02:46.233
OH, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

02:46.233 --> 02:50.303
I WOULD GO WITH ANYONE.

02:50.303 --> 02:51.571
HMM.

02:51.571 --> 02:52.973
HMM.

02:52.973 --> 02:53.974
HMM.

02:53.974 --> 02:54.608
HMM.

02:54.608 --> 02:55.742
HMM.
HMM.

02:55.742 --> 02:57.411
NO, I GUESS --

02:57.411 --> 02:58.612
THANK YOU!

02:58.612 --> 03:00.013
OH, MAN!

03:00.013 --> 03:02.182
NEVER WOULD'VE EVEN DREAMED
OF ASKING YOU,

03:02.182 --> 03:04.217
BUT SINCE YOU VOLUNTEERED --
NO TAKE-BACKS.

03:04.217 --> 03:06.286
YOU'RE AN ANGEL IN
A DEVIL'S BODY. I LOVE YOU.

03:06.286 --> 03:07.688
JACKIE, I CAN'T GO.

03:07.688 --> 03:09.990
I'M BABYSITTING BERT
TONIGHT, SO --
AH, DON'T WORRY.

03:09.990 --> 03:12.292
I KNEW YOU'D USE THAT AS
AN EXCUSE, SO I ALREADY
LINED UP A BABYSITTER.

03:12.292 --> 03:13.293
SO CHOP-CHOP.

03:13.293 --> 03:16.463
LOOK AT ALL THESE SPICES.

03:16.463 --> 03:18.198
AH! MEG, LOOK.

03:18.198 --> 03:19.700
[ CHUCKLING ]
GROSS.

03:19.700 --> 03:21.368
TEVIN, IT'S PRONOUNCED
"CUE-MIN."

03:21.368 --> 03:23.370
[ CAR HORN HONKS ]

03:23.370 --> 03:24.371
ALL RIGHT.

03:24.371 --> 03:26.173
JACKIE'S HERE.
I GOT TO GO.

03:26.173 --> 03:28.041
[ CAR HORN HONKS ]

03:28.041 --> 03:29.976
[ SIGHS ]
MEG, TEVIN, BE GOOD.

03:29.976 --> 03:31.144
BERT, YOU'RE IN CHARGE.

03:31.144 --> 03:32.179
FINALLY.

03:32.179 --> 03:34.047
[ CAR HORN HONKS ]

03:34.047 --> 03:35.682
OH, GOD,
IT'S GONNA BE A LONG NIGHT.

03:35.682 --> 03:38.485
AH. THE THINGS THAT YOU DO FOR
YOUR HUSBAND'S SECOND EX-WIFE.

03:38.485 --> 03:41.388
WHERE DO YOU THINK
THE BOOZE IS?
I DON'T KNOW.

03:41.388 --> 03:45.559
MAN:
THE MIGHTY INCA EMPIRE FELL
NOT BECAUSE OF WAR OR FAMINE,

03:45.559 --> 03:47.360
BUT BECAUSE OF SOMETHING
FAR MORE INSIDIOUS.

03:47.360 --> 03:48.762
HE'S ASLEEP.

03:48.762 --> 03:51.498
FINALLY. OKAY.
WHAT'S THE PLAN?

03:51.498 --> 03:54.301
SO, I'LL TAKE HILLARY
TO ORIENTATION.
JUST YOU? WHY?

03:54.301 --> 03:57.070
BECAUSE YOUR CONTRIBUTION TO
OUR CHILDREN'S EDUCATION ENDED

03:57.070 --> 03:59.306
WHEN THEY MASTERED
PAPIER-MÂCHÉ VOLCANOS.

03:59.306 --> 04:00.307
I STAND BY THEIR WORK.

04:00.307 --> 04:01.608
THAT WAS 10 YEARS AGO,
PETE.

04:01.608 --> 04:03.376
AH, WELL, I AM PICKING
THE BATON BACK UP.

04:03.376 --> 04:06.513
THIS TRIP, I'M GONNA GET WARREN
EXCITED ABOUT COLLEGE.

04:06.513 --> 04:08.215
OKAY, GOOD!
GET HIM EXCITED!

04:08.215 --> 04:10.250
GET HIM EXCITED ENOUGH
TO STUDY NOW,

04:10.250 --> 04:13.120
AND MAYBE HE WON'T HAVE TO GO TO
A COLLEGE THAT ADVERTISES ON TV.

04:14.387 --> 04:15.989
YOU KNOW,
I'M GLAD I CAME.

04:15.989 --> 04:18.225
I CAN'T WAIT TO MEET SOME
OF YOUR HIGH-SCHOOL FRIENDS.

04:18.225 --> 04:22.062
OH, WELL, WE WERE JUST A PACK
OF CARDS WITH ONLY ONE JOKER.

04:23.029 --> 04:25.365
OH, THERE'S THIS ONE GIRL --
MARCY.

04:25.365 --> 04:28.201
WHEW! SHE AND I USED TO
GIVE EACH OTHER THE STUFF.

04:28.201 --> 04:30.036
OOH! LIKE DRUGS?

04:30.036 --> 04:31.004
NO! NO!

04:31.004 --> 04:32.139
THE BUSINESS, YOU KNOW?

04:32.139 --> 04:34.074
THE CHEESE.

04:34.074 --> 04:35.342
THE OL' BACK AND FORTH.

04:35.342 --> 04:37.043
I'D ZIG, SHE'D ZAG.

04:37.043 --> 04:38.411
[ LAUGHS ]

04:38.411 --> 04:40.313
WE'D BE AT IT ALL DAY.

04:40.313 --> 04:42.082
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

04:42.082 --> 04:43.183
I GET IT.

04:43.183 --> 04:44.184
DRUGS.

04:44.184 --> 04:46.520
YEAH, SOMETIMES.
YEAH.

04:46.520 --> 04:47.587
THIS IS FUN.

04:47.587 --> 04:49.289
GOD, I'D MUCH RATHER
BE HERE WITH YOU

04:49.289 --> 04:51.458
THAN WITH DIANE,
THE ICE QUEEN.

04:51.458 --> 04:53.593
OOH! BRRRR!
FROSTY.

04:53.593 --> 04:56.263
YEAH. THE ONLY THING COLDER
THAN HER HEART IS HER --

04:56.263 --> 04:57.364
AAH!
[ HORN HONKS ]

04:57.364 --> 04:59.366
AAH!

04:59.366 --> 05:01.668
HITTING A SQUIRREL
IS GOOD LUCK, RIGHT?

05:03.103 --> 05:05.305
A RABBIT AND TURTLE...

05:05.305 --> 05:06.973
GO IN THE HOLE...

05:06.973 --> 05:08.108
TIE THEM.

05:10.243 --> 05:12.179
LOOK AT ME.
I'M PETE.

05:12.179 --> 05:13.680
I'M A GROWN-UP.

05:13.680 --> 05:15.448
LOOK AT ME.
I'M KATE.

05:15.448 --> 05:18.051
PETE, HAVE YOUR WAY WITH ME
BEFORE YOU DIE.

05:18.051 --> 05:19.986
WE'RE SO GOOD AT THIS.

05:19.986 --> 05:20.987
[ GASPS ]

05:20.987 --> 05:22.022
LET'S HAVE A KID.

05:22.022 --> 05:23.590
THAT'S
A REALLY BIG DECISION.

05:23.590 --> 05:25.392
LET'S DO IT.

05:28.361 --> 05:29.763
HI. I'M ADELE.

05:29.763 --> 05:31.164
WHOA.

05:31.164 --> 05:33.700
ARE WE
IN THE RIGHT HOUSE?

05:33.700 --> 05:35.602
THIS IS MY SECOND
BEST FRIEND -- ADELE.

05:35.602 --> 05:38.171
SINCE YOU GUYS WOULDN'T LET ME
PLAY DRESS-UP WITH YOU,

05:38.171 --> 05:39.339
I INVITED HER OVER.

05:39.339 --> 05:41.141
I KNOW HOW TO COUNT
IN KOREAN.

05:41.141 --> 05:42.275
HANA, DUL.

05:42.275 --> 05:44.277
I CAN COUNT TO THREE
IN BURP.

05:44.277 --> 05:46.279
[ BURPING ]
ONE, TWO, THREE.

05:46.279 --> 05:47.447
BERT: OH, MY GOD!

05:47.447 --> 05:48.748
THAT IS SO COOL!

05:48.748 --> 05:51.985
YOU HAVE GOTS TO TEACH ME
HOW TO DO THAT!

05:51.985 --> 05:52.752
NO PROBLEM.

05:52.752 --> 05:55.088
UM, MEG,
GRAB A COUPLE OF SODAS.

05:55.088 --> 05:56.556
OKAY.
OH, WAIT. UH...

05:56.556 --> 06:00.393
KATE SAID SOMETHING ABOUT
DRINKING OR NOT DRINKING SODAS.

06:00.393 --> 06:03.230
OH, SHE SAID I COULD.
YEAH, I'M PRETTY SURE IT WAS
A LIST OF THINGS THAT WERE FINE.

06:03.230 --> 06:04.197
YEAH.

06:05.432 --> 06:07.267
WHEN YOU SAID,
"LET'S GO VISIT THE BOOKSTORE,"

06:07.267 --> 06:08.535
I GOT ALL NERVOUS,

06:08.535 --> 06:10.470
BUT ALL THAT PLACE SOLD
WAS CANDY AND SWEATSHIRTS.

06:10.470 --> 06:12.405
SEE, BUDDY? ISN'T COLLEGE
A MAGICAL PLACE?

06:12.405 --> 06:15.342
[ LAUGHS ] I HAD NO IDEA
HOW MUCH IT HAD TO OFFER.

06:15.342 --> 06:17.510
LIKE, DID YOU SEE THAT GUY
IN THE CAFETERIA?

06:19.212 --> 06:21.381
I'M GONNA NEED A LITTLE MORE
INFORMATION, BUDDY.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.750
HE MIXED LIKE FIVE DIFFERENT
CEREALS INTO ONE BOWL.

06:23.750 --> 06:26.753
AND THAT OTHER DUDE WHO
PUT CHOCOLATE MILK INTO
HIS FROSTY FLAKES?

06:26.753 --> 06:28.555
HA!
[ IMITATES EXPLOSION ]

06:28.555 --> 06:32.692
DID ANYTHING NON-CEREAL-BASED
CAPTURE YOUR IMAGINATION?

06:32.692 --> 06:33.693
MM...

06:33.693 --> 06:35.028
YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:35.028 --> 06:36.396
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

06:36.396 --> 06:39.766
I-I-I'M EXCITED THAT
YOU'RE EXCITED TO STUDY HARD NOW

06:39.766 --> 06:41.568
SO ONE DAY
YOU CAN GO TO COLLEGE.

06:41.568 --> 06:42.435
YEAH.

06:43.703 --> 06:46.072
BUT, I MEAN, I GUESS I ALREADY
HAVE ALL THE CLOTHES,

06:46.072 --> 06:48.708
AND I CAN JUST PUT CHOCOLATE
MILK IN MY CEREAL AT HOME

06:48.708 --> 06:50.210
NOW THAT I'VE LEARNED
THAT TRICK.

06:50.210 --> 06:52.545
IS THERE ANYTHING MORE
FOR ME TO GAIN FROM THIS PLACE?

06:52.545 --> 06:55.048
THE LADIES?

06:55.048 --> 06:56.016
NOW YOU'RE TALKIN'.

06:56.016 --> 06:57.050
RIGHT?

06:57.050 --> 07:00.053
LET'S GO FIND MOM AND HIL.
COME ON.

07:00.987 --> 07:03.023
[ SIGHS ]

07:03.023 --> 07:06.126
HILLARY: [ SIGHS ]
IT IS SO COOL TO BE IN A ROOM

07:06.126 --> 07:08.128
WITH KIDS
ALMOST AS SMART AS ME.

07:08.128 --> 07:09.095
AWW.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.665
OH, SEEING YOU
THIS EXCITED

07:11.665 --> 07:14.534
MAKES THE CAR RIDE WITH
YOUR FATHER ALMOST WORTH IT.

07:14.534 --> 07:16.002
WELCOME, EVERYBODY.

07:16.002 --> 07:19.072
TO KICK THINGS OFF,
LET'S ALL GO AROUND THE ROOM

07:19.072 --> 07:22.475
AND SAY ONE ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENT
WE ARE MOST PROUD OF THIS YEAR.

07:22.475 --> 07:24.678
UH, CONSIDER
THE ICE BROKEN.

07:24.678 --> 07:29.282
I AM DR. DIANE BUCKLEY,
AND I HAVE HAD QUITE A YEAR.

07:29.282 --> 07:30.717
OH, JUST THE CAMPERS.

07:30.717 --> 07:32.385
OH, YES, OF COURSE.

07:32.385 --> 07:36.356
I WAS ONLY GOING TO INTRODUCE
MY EXTRAORDINARY DAUGHTER.

07:36.356 --> 07:37.424
THANKS, MOM.

07:37.424 --> 07:38.692
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:38.692 --> 07:39.759
HELLO.

07:39.759 --> 07:42.329
MY NAME IS
HILLARY RODHAM HARRISON,

07:42.329 --> 07:45.765
AND I HAD A POEM PUBLISHED
IN MY SCHOOL'S LITERARY MAGAZINE

07:45.765 --> 07:47.567
CALLED "SEASONS."

07:49.002 --> 07:52.138
I'M ALEX, AND I WAS
ALSO RECENTLY PUBLISHED,

07:52.138 --> 07:54.307
IN THE JOURNAL OF THE
AMERICAN MEDICAL ASSOCIATION.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.042
OH.

07:56.042 --> 07:58.044
HI. MY NAME
IS BADISHA.

07:58.044 --> 08:01.114
YOU PROBABLY ALREADY KNOW ME
FROM MY T.E.D. TALK.

08:01.114 --> 08:03.483
THESE KIDS
ARE REALLY SMART.

08:03.483 --> 08:04.985
SO ARE YOU.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.987
GIVE A DIFFERENT FACT.

08:09.756 --> 08:11.491
I'D LIKE TO CHANGE
MY FACT.

08:11.491 --> 08:16.696
J'AI LU "MADAME BOVARY"
DANS LE FRANÇAIS D'ORIGINE.

08:16.696 --> 08:18.765
WOW. YOU'RE SO LUCKY.

08:18.765 --> 08:21.668
I WAS ONLY ALLOWED TO LEARN
LANGUAGES OF THE FUTURE --

08:21.668 --> 08:24.571
MANDARIN, ARABIC, HTML,
JAVA, UNIX.

08:25.672 --> 08:27.207
IT'S OKAY.
EXCUSEZ-MOI.

08:30.210 --> 08:32.078
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:32.078 --> 08:33.713
HERE'S MINE.
HERE'S YOURS.

08:33.713 --> 08:36.049
THANKS SO MUCH
FOR COMING, KATE.

08:36.049 --> 08:37.250
"KATE FISHER"?

08:37.250 --> 08:39.019
THEY PUT YOUR LAST NAME
ON MINE.
OH.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.720
I'LL -- I'LL JUST
HAVE THEM CHANGE IT.

08:40.720 --> 08:42.756
NO, NO, NO.
SHE'S REALLY SLAMMED.

08:42.756 --> 08:44.724
LET'S NOT
BOTHER HER.

08:44.724 --> 08:45.992
JACKIE!

08:45.992 --> 08:48.061
CONGRATULATIONS,
YOU TWO.

08:48.061 --> 08:49.362
I'LL SEE YOU
ON THE DANCE FLOOR.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.031
OH, THANKS, MARCY.
COOL.
OKAY.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.432
SHE SEEMS REALLY SWEET.
YEAH.

08:52.432 --> 08:54.034
WHAT IS SHE
CONGRATULATING US ABOUT?

08:54.034 --> 08:55.335
OUR WEDDING.

08:55.335 --> 08:57.137
I TOLD EVERYONE
WE'RE MARRIED.

08:57.137 --> 08:59.105
MARRIED?
YEAH.

08:59.105 --> 09:01.241
WHAT? JACKIE!
COME ON, LET'S GET
A DRINK AND WE'LL TALK
ABOUT IT LATER, OKAY?

09:01.241 --> 09:03.343
NO, DON'T.
I WANT US TO HAVE FUN.
JUST --

09:03.343 --> 09:04.577
JACKIE, NOT --
STOP IT.

09:04.577 --> 09:07.547
OKAY, LET ME LAND
OR I'M MOVING TO THE FRONT.

09:09.688 --> 09:12.323
OKAY, I'M SORRY
THAT I DIDN'T TELL YOU SOONER.

09:12.323 --> 09:13.853
IT JUST NEVER SEEMED
LIKE THE RIGHT TIME.

09:13.853 --> 09:16.356
OH, REALLY? WE ONLY SPENT
SIX HOURS TOGETHER IN A CAR.

09:16.356 --> 09:17.690
THERE WASN'T TIME TO SAY,
"HEY, KATE,

09:17.690 --> 09:19.325
I TOLD EVERYONE AT THE REUNION
THAT YOU'RE MY WIFE"?

09:19.325 --> 09:21.394
WELL, WE WERE TALKING
ABOUT DREAM LICENSE PLATES.

09:22.228 --> 09:23.263
LOOK, LISTEN.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.298
HIGH SCHOOL FOR ME
WAS NO PICNIC.

09:25.298 --> 09:27.100
I DIDN'T HAVE
THAT MANY FRIENDS,

09:27.100 --> 09:28.101
NO ONE WANTED
TO EAT WITH ME,

09:28.101 --> 09:29.836
SO I HAD TO EAT OUTSIDE
BY MYSELF,

09:29.836 --> 09:32.972
WHICH I KNOW SOUNDS LIKE
A PICNIC, BUT IT REALLY WASN'T.

09:32.972 --> 09:35.041
YEAH, AND REMEMBER
THAT BILLY GOAT MARCY,

09:35.041 --> 09:37.210
THE ONE WHO CAME OVER
GNAWING ON THAT TIN CAN?

09:37.210 --> 09:38.311
YEAH. SHE SEEMED NICE.

09:38.311 --> 09:40.213
YEAH, NICE --
FOR A DONKEY.

09:40.213 --> 09:42.081
I THOUGHT SHE WAS PRETTY.

09:42.081 --> 09:44.017
WELL, PROBABLY 'CAUSE
HER TRAINER GROOMED
HER FOR THE REUNION.

09:44.017 --> 09:45.551
STUPID COW!

09:45.551 --> 09:48.187
OKAY, JACKIE, CAN YOU JUST PICK
AN ANIMAL AND FINISH THE STORY?

09:48.187 --> 09:50.490
HER AND HER FRIENDS
WERE SO MEAN TO ME.

09:50.490 --> 09:52.258
THEY USED TO MAKE FUN OF ME
ALL THE TIME,

09:52.258 --> 09:54.093
MAINLY BECAUSE OF
MY MOUTH-BREATHING,

09:54.093 --> 09:56.062
BUT ALSO BECAUSE
I NEVER HAD A BOYFRIEND.

09:56.062 --> 09:57.263
AND FINALLY,
I GOT SICK OF IT.

09:57.263 --> 09:59.599
I DON'T KNOW.
I JUST CAME OUT.

09:59.599 --> 10:01.134
AND HOW DID THAT FIX IT?

10:01.134 --> 10:02.268
BECAUSE IT WAS
THE EARLY '90S.

10:02.268 --> 10:04.237
IT WAS A GREAT TIME
TO PRETEND TO BE GAY.

10:04.237 --> 10:06.105
THAT WHOLE P.C. THING,
REMEMBER?

10:06.105 --> 10:07.273
WHITE PEOPLE
IN DASHIKIS.

10:07.273 --> 10:08.341
OH, MY GOD.

10:08.341 --> 10:09.208
[ GASPS ]
OH!

10:09.208 --> 10:10.243
IS THAT FOR REAL?

10:10.243 --> 10:12.245
AH! IT'S ME!
THAT'S MY PROM PHOTO!

10:12.245 --> 10:17.250
OH! LOOK HOW HANDSOME
AND CUTE I WAS, SO YOUNG.

10:17.250 --> 10:18.551
I MEAN, I KNOW
IT WASN'T MY DREAM PROM,

10:18.551 --> 10:20.019
BUT HEY,
WE CAN'T ALL BE MARCY,

10:20.019 --> 10:21.487
AND I GET IT IF YOU
DON'T WANT TO BE MY WIFE.

10:21.487 --> 10:22.989
THAT'S JUST FINE,
YOU BILLY GOAT.

10:22.989 --> 10:24.190
NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL DO IT.

10:24.190 --> 10:25.925
WAIT. WHAT?
YEAH.

10:25.925 --> 10:27.427
I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

10:27.427 --> 10:31.564
LISTEN, NONE OF US GOT OUT
OF A HIGH SCHOOL UNSCATHED.
NO.

10:31.564 --> 10:34.000
JUST CLEAR YOUR CRAZY WITH ME
FIRST NEXT TIME, OKAY?
OKAY. OKAY.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.568
OKAY?
MM-HMM.

10:35.568 --> 10:37.937
NOW LET'S GO SHOW EVERYONE
HOW GREAT THINGS TURNED OUT

10:37.937 --> 10:39.272
FOR THIS BRAVE,
LITTLE MOUTH-BREATHER.

10:39.272 --> 10:41.507
OKAY.
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

10:45.244 --> 10:47.547
I'M HANGING OUT AT COLLEGE,
POUNDING CEREAL,

10:47.547 --> 10:49.215
AND YOU TAKE ME
TO CLASS?

10:49.215 --> 10:51.050
I'M NOT REALLY
DIGGING THIS.

10:51.050 --> 10:53.519
BUT I WAS DIGGING THAT VENDING
MACHINE WITH THE COMB IN IT.

10:53.519 --> 10:55.188
HEY, CAN I HAVE
THREE BUCKS?

10:55.188 --> 10:57.056
YOU ALREADY HAVE A COMB.

10:57.056 --> 10:59.559
AND I THINK
YOU MIGHT LIKE THIS CLASS.

11:00.827 --> 11:04.864
FROM "RAMBO" TO "BAMBI,"
WELCOME TO VIOLENCE IN CINEMA.

11:04.864 --> 11:05.832
SHUT UP!

11:06.332 --> 11:08.301
OH, OH.
SORRY. SORRY.

11:08.301 --> 11:10.236
PLEASE CONTINUE.

11:10.236 --> 11:13.973
[ BURPING ]
FOUR...FIVE.

11:13.973 --> 11:15.875
[ LAUGHS ] NICE ONE!

11:15.875 --> 11:18.344
FULL-BODIED AND...
IT SMELLS.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.213
DRINKING SODA'S
SO MUCH FUN.

11:20.213 --> 11:22.215
I FEEL LIKE MY TEETH
ARE GETTING SMALLER.

11:23.983 --> 11:25.184
ALL RIGHT, RODENTS.

11:25.184 --> 11:27.286
MAC AND CHEESE ORANGE,
MAC AND CHEESE WHITE,

11:27.286 --> 11:29.155
DINO NUGGET,
CHICKEN STARS.

11:31.024 --> 11:32.191
OH, AND FRUIT.

11:33.259 --> 11:35.028
COME HERE.

11:35.028 --> 11:37.430
SO, I FOUND WHERE THEY KEEP
THEIR NICE WINE.

11:37.430 --> 11:39.232
LET'S POP ONE
AND GET WEIRD.

11:39.232 --> 11:42.068
MEG, WE'RE ALWAYS HANGING OUT
WITH YOUR FRIENDS.

11:42.068 --> 11:44.337
LET'S HANG OUT WITH MY FRIENDS
FOR A CHANGE.

11:44.337 --> 11:45.872
BERT AND ADELE
ARE COOL.

11:45.872 --> 11:47.040
THEY'RE 8.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.808
I'M 8 1/2.

11:48.808 --> 11:50.810
AH! SWEET, ADELE!
I'M 31 1/2.

11:50.810 --> 11:53.212
YET ANOTHER THING
WE HAVE IN COMMON.

11:53.212 --> 11:56.916
HAVE YOU EVEN TRIED
TO GET TO KNOW THEM?

11:58.551 --> 12:00.920
SO, WE'RE ON OUR HONEYMOON
IN TULUM...

12:00.920 --> 12:02.889
AND WE'RE TOPLESS
THE WHOLE TIME.

12:02.889 --> 12:04.257
E-EVERYONE'S TOPLESS.
YEAH.

12:04.257 --> 12:07.226
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN, IT STARTS
RAINING OUT OF NOWHERE.

12:07.226 --> 12:09.896
OH! THIS ONE WANTS AVOCADO
ALL OF A SUDDEN.

12:09.896 --> 12:11.831
I'M LIKE, "OH, NO."
AND SHE --

12:11.831 --> 12:13.332
ANYWAY,
LONG STORY SHORT,

12:13.332 --> 12:15.401
WE JUST END UP MAKING LOVE
ALL NIGHT LONG.

12:15.401 --> 12:17.870
OKAY. I'M GONNA HIT
THE LADIES' ROOM.

12:17.870 --> 12:19.138
OH, OKAY.

12:19.138 --> 12:22.208
WELL, WE'LL JUST WATCH
THAT TUCHUS GO. MMM!

12:23.543 --> 12:24.444
KATE!

12:24.444 --> 12:26.145
OH, HI.
HI.

12:26.145 --> 12:28.481
IT'S SO NICE
SEEING JACKIE SO HAPPY.
MM-HMM.

12:28.481 --> 12:31.384
IT'S ONE THING TO HEAR ABOUT
HER SUCCESSFUL PICKLE BUSINESS,

12:31.384 --> 12:34.454
BUT TO FIND SOMEONE
TO SHARE IT WITH...
YEAH.

12:34.454 --> 12:37.156
YOU KNOW, I WOULDN'T EVEN
CALL IT A BUSINESS.

12:37.156 --> 12:39.959
"PICKLE ME THIS"
IS MORE OF AN EMPIRE, SO...
YEAH.

12:39.959 --> 12:43.996
AND YOU FOUND YOURSELF
A PRETTY SWEET SITUATION, HUH?

12:43.996 --> 12:44.931
RIGHT.

12:44.931 --> 12:46.165
[ LAUGHS ]

12:46.165 --> 12:47.133
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

12:47.133 --> 12:49.235
OH, COME ON.
JACKIE TOLD ME.

12:50.169 --> 12:51.404
SHE MAKES THE MONEY,

12:51.404 --> 12:53.072
AND YOU STAY HOME
AND KEEP IT RIGHT AND TIGHT.

12:53.072 --> 12:55.575
HER WORDS, NOT MINE.

12:55.575 --> 12:57.310
THAT'S MY WIFE JOKING.

12:57.310 --> 13:00.179
JOKING, I MEAN,
'CAUSE...I DO THINGS.

13:00.179 --> 13:01.280
I DO THINGS.

13:01.280 --> 13:02.849
I DO IMPORTANT THINGS.

13:02.849 --> 13:04.250
OH, I'M SORRY.

13:04.250 --> 13:05.184
LIKE WHAT?

13:05.184 --> 13:07.053
OH, LIKE WHAT?
MM-HMM.

13:07.053 --> 13:09.288
WEL-- WELL, I CAN'T BELIEVE
SHE DIDN'T TELL YOU.

13:09.288 --> 13:13.025
I MEAN, LIKE, TODAY I WOKE UP
AT 4:15 A.M.,

13:13.025 --> 13:14.494
IN THE MORNING...
MM-HMM.

13:14.494 --> 13:17.196
...TO GET UP AND GO
AND REATTACH A FLOATING PATELLA

13:17.196 --> 13:19.132
WITH A CADAVER LIGAMENT
TO A FAT MAN.

13:19.132 --> 13:22.869
YEP, AND I DID THAT BECAUSE
I AM AN ORTHOPEDIC SURGEON

13:22.869 --> 13:24.203
WHO WENT TO STANFORD.

13:24.203 --> 13:25.104
THAT'S RIGHT.

13:25.104 --> 13:26.439
NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

13:26.439 --> 13:28.808
I'VE BEEN NEEDING TO GO PEE
FOR THE PAST 10 MINUTES.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.877
SO, YOU KNOW,
WHEN I HOLD IT IN...

13:30.877 --> 13:32.879
PEOPLE DIE.

13:36.449 --> 13:38.050
THAT WAS SO AWESOME!

13:38.050 --> 13:39.252
THAT ONE GUY
WAS LIKE...

13:39.252 --> 13:40.820
[ IMITATES MACHINE GUN
FIRING ]

13:40.820 --> 13:42.255
AND THE OTHER GUY
WAS LIKE...

13:42.255 --> 13:44.190
[ IMITATES SWORD
CLANGING ]

13:44.190 --> 13:45.825
OH! THAT WAS SO COOL!

13:45.825 --> 13:47.293
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M GONNA DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES TO GET HERE,

13:47.293 --> 13:50.229
EVEN IF THAT MEANS STUDYING
FIVE HOURS EVERY WEEK.

13:50.229 --> 13:52.265
WELL, MAKE SURE
AND SCHEDULE SOME "ME" TIME.

13:52.265 --> 13:55.168
I'LL ALWAYS
HAVE TIME FOR YOU.

13:55.168 --> 13:55.935
MWAH.

13:55.935 --> 13:57.470
WHOO! COLLEGE!

13:57.470 --> 13:58.571
HEAR THAT?

13:58.571 --> 14:00.873
THE SOUND OF ME CRUSHING IT
AS A DAD.

14:00.873 --> 14:03.176
OH, NO, NO.
THOSE ARE MINE, TOO.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.811
HILLARY,
THREE PLATES OF FRIES?

14:05.811 --> 14:06.579
SWEETHEART?

14:06.579 --> 14:08.247
WHO CARES?

14:08.247 --> 14:09.849
HEY, SWEETIE,
HOW WAS SCIENCE...

14:09.849 --> 14:11.250
MY LIFE IS OVER!

14:11.250 --> 14:12.318
WHOOP.

14:13.386 --> 14:15.188
...CAMP.

14:15.188 --> 14:16.522
HOW DO I PUT THIS?

14:16.522 --> 14:19.258
IS AUNT PERIOD IN TOWN?

14:19.258 --> 14:20.393
OH, PETER, IT WAS AWFUL.

14:20.393 --> 14:21.961
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN OUR DAUGHTER'S LIFE,

14:21.961 --> 14:23.496
SHE WASN'T THE SMARTEST PERSON
IN THE ROOM,

14:23.496 --> 14:25.331
AND THERE WAS NOTHING
I COULD DO TO HELP HER.

14:25.331 --> 14:27.099
DID YOU TALK TO HER?
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

14:27.099 --> 14:28.868
I FROZE UP.

14:28.868 --> 14:30.503
I TRIED TO DRAW
ON PERSONAL EXPERIENCE,

14:30.503 --> 14:32.972
BUT THE ONLY FAILURE
I COULD THINK OF IN THE MOMENT

14:32.972 --> 14:34.106
WAS MY INABILITY
TO ORGASM

14:34.106 --> 14:36.142
DURING THE LATTER PART
OF OUR MARRIAGE,

14:36.142 --> 14:38.044
WHICH IS, OF COURSE,
REALLY YOUR FAILURE.

14:38.044 --> 14:39.412
I NEVER HAD A CHANCE.

14:39.412 --> 14:41.480
YOU KEPT SWATTING MY HAND AWAY
SAYING, "WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

14:41.480 --> 14:43.049
YOU HAVE NO PLAN."

14:43.049 --> 14:44.217
I JUST WISH
I HAD TAUGHT HER

14:44.217 --> 14:46.018
THAT IT WAS OKAY
TO BE SECOND-BEST.

14:47.587 --> 14:50.323
WELL, I MEAN,
IT'S NOT ALL PICKLES.
IT'S BEETS, IT'S RELISH.

14:50.323 --> 14:52.925
YOU KNOW, BUT I'M KIND
OF THINKING OF GETTING
INTO THE CHUTNEY GAME.

14:52.925 --> 14:54.193
EXCUSE ME.
JACKIE.

14:54.193 --> 14:55.561
OH, HEY, SUGAR BOOBIES.
WHERE YOU BEEN ALL MY LIFE?

14:55.561 --> 14:56.963
KIDDING. WE'RE MARRIED.

14:56.963 --> 14:58.431
I BAGGED THIS
HOT, LITTLE -- OW!

14:58.431 --> 15:01.100
OW! THAT'S HOW I LIKE IT --
ROUGH.
JACKIE, ENOUGH.

15:01.100 --> 15:03.202
I DO YOU A FAVOR, AND YOU
GO AROUND TELLING PEOPLE

15:03.202 --> 15:04.270
THAT I'M JUST
YOUR ARM CANDY?

15:04.270 --> 15:05.404
DO YOU KNOW
HOW THAT MAKES ME FEEL?

15:05.404 --> 15:07.573
I HAD TO TELL MARCY
THAT I WAS A SURGEON.

15:07.573 --> 15:10.176
OOH! AAH! I WISH YOU HAD KINDA
CLEARED THAT WITH ME FIRST.

15:10.176 --> 15:12.478
IT'S NOT REALLY GONNA JIVE WITH
THE STORIES I'VE BEEN TELLING.

15:12.478 --> 15:13.813
DON'T KNOW
TOO MANY DOCTORS

15:13.813 --> 15:15.414
THAT WOULD SLAP
A TOLL-BOOTH OPERATOR.

15:15.414 --> 15:16.449
HMM.
WHAT?

15:16.449 --> 15:18.184
JACKIE, YOU COULD'VE
MADE ME ANYONE.

15:18.184 --> 15:19.318
WHAT ABOUT
A CAREER WOMAN?

15:19.318 --> 15:20.486
OH, MAN.
WHAT? WHY?
WHAT? WHAT?

15:20.486 --> 15:22.088
YOU DON'T THINK PEOPLE
WOULD BELIEVE THAT?

15:22.088 --> 15:23.956
HEY, GIRL,
WHEN I GO TO YOUR REUNION,

15:23.956 --> 15:25.491
I'LL BE ANY KIND OF WIFE
YOU WANT,

15:25.491 --> 15:29.228
SO JUST RELAX, HAVE A DRINK,
AND KEEP LOOKING SO DAMN PRETTY.

15:29.228 --> 15:30.396
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

15:30.396 --> 15:31.330
UNBELIEVABLE.

15:31.330 --> 15:33.232
WHAT?
THAT WAS A COMPLIMENT.

15:33.232 --> 15:34.433
[ SIGHS ]

15:34.433 --> 15:36.302
WOMEN, HUH? UGH.

15:36.302 --> 15:39.272
YOU CAN'T -- OKAY.

15:41.427 --> 15:43.476
KATE, WAIT!

15:43.476 --> 15:46.345
LOOK, I'M SORRY
WHAT I SAID ABOUT YOU.

15:46.345 --> 15:48.214
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TELL EVERYONE
THAT YOU'RE A DOCTOR.

15:48.214 --> 15:51.117
OH! THAT YOU WERE VOTED HOTTEST
SURGEON IN GOOD DOCTOR MAGAZINE.

15:51.117 --> 15:52.551
THAT'S THE PROBLEM,
JACKIE.

15:52.551 --> 15:53.853
I'M NOT A SURGEON,
OKAY?

15:53.853 --> 15:54.987
I DON'T EVEN WORK.

15:54.987 --> 15:56.222
I GO TO YOGA
TWICE A WEEK

15:56.222 --> 15:58.424
AND I SOMETIMES STILL HAVE
BERT MAKE ME DINNER.

15:58.424 --> 16:00.559
SO? WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

16:00.559 --> 16:02.295
I DIDN'T FINISH COLLEGE,
OKAY?

16:02.295 --> 16:05.364
AND THIS MORNING I LIED TO DIANE
AND I TOLD HER THAT I DID.

16:05.364 --> 16:08.234
SO YOU TOLD ONE LITTLE LIE
ABOUT COLLEGE.

16:08.234 --> 16:09.935
BIG WHOOP. HA!

16:09.935 --> 16:12.071
I TRICKED YOU
INTO BEING MY WIFE,

16:12.071 --> 16:14.874
AND I JUST INVITED 10 PEOPLE
TO COME TOUR MY PICKLE FACTORY.

16:14.874 --> 16:16.942
BUT THAT'S THE POINT,
JACKIE.

16:16.942 --> 16:20.212
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE TO LIE
ABOUT GOING TO COLLEGE

16:20.212 --> 16:21.347
OR BEING A DOCTOR.

16:21.347 --> 16:23.449
I WANT TO ACTUALLY
DO SOMETHING.

16:23.449 --> 16:24.884
RIGHT ON!

16:24.884 --> 16:26.385
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU SHOULDN'T LIE, EITHER.

16:26.385 --> 16:29.355
BECAUSE YOUR REAL LIFE IS LIKE
A HUNDRED TIMES MORE INTERESTING

16:29.355 --> 16:31.090
THAN ANYBODY ELSE'S
IN THERE.

16:31.090 --> 16:32.358
YEAH. YOU'RE RIGHT.

16:32.358 --> 16:33.993
I AM AMAZING.

16:33.993 --> 16:35.494
I'M A GREAT, STRAIGHT,
SINGLE LADY

16:35.494 --> 16:38.164
WITH A BOUTIQUE PICKLE BUSINESS
THAT FITS RIGHT IN MY TRUNK.

16:38.164 --> 16:39.265
YEAH!

16:39.265 --> 16:41.200
IT WAS REALLY NICE
BEING THE COOL GIRL

16:41.200 --> 16:42.868
AT THE PARTY, THOUGH,
FOR ONCE.

16:42.868 --> 16:44.837
YOU KNOW WHAT --
YOU ARE WAY COOLER

16:44.837 --> 16:46.572
THAN YOU GIVE YOURSELF
CREDIT FOR, J-BIRD.

16:46.572 --> 16:47.506
YEAH?

16:47.506 --> 16:48.808
YEAH.
AWW.

16:48.808 --> 16:50.276
COME ON,
LET'S GET OUTTA HERE.

16:50.276 --> 16:51.010
YEAH.

16:51.877 --> 16:52.945
OH, NO, JACKIE!

16:52.945 --> 16:54.347
OKAY, I GOT TO BE HONEST
WITH YOU.

16:54.347 --> 16:56.148
YOU'RE JUST SENDING ME
MIXED SIGNALS ALL NIGHT.

16:56.148 --> 16:58.584
HAVE I?
YEAH.

16:58.584 --> 17:00.119
HIL, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

17:00.119 --> 17:02.154
YOU'RE THE SMARTEST PERSON
I'VE EVER MET.
[ SCOFFS ]

17:02.154 --> 17:04.490
IN A YEAR, YOU'RE GONNA BLOW
ALL THOSE KIDS OUT OF THE WATER.

17:04.490 --> 17:06.959
REALLY?
LET ME TELL YOU
ABOUT A GIRL I KNOW.

17:06.959 --> 17:09.028
THAT GIRL CAN DO ANYTHING
SHE PUTS HER MIND TO.

17:09.028 --> 17:12.031
THAT GIRL IS BRILLIANT, ALTHOUGH
SHE MAY NOT ALWAYS REALIZE IT.

17:12.031 --> 17:14.333
THAT GIRL'S MY HERO.

17:14.333 --> 17:15.301
THANKS, WARREN.

17:15.301 --> 17:16.402
OH, DON'T INTERRUPT ME.

17:16.402 --> 17:17.937
THAT GIRL
WON THE HUNGER GAMES.

17:17.937 --> 17:20.005
WAIT. KATNISS?

17:20.005 --> 17:21.140
OH, YEAH! KATNISS.

17:21.140 --> 17:22.975
YEAH, I KNEW HER NAME
STARTED WITH A "K."

17:22.975 --> 17:25.010
HA. SHE'S SO HOT.
YOU'RE PRETTY COOL YOURSELF.

17:25.010 --> 17:26.579
HEY, SWEETIE,
YOU DOING BETTER?

17:26.579 --> 17:28.848
YEAH.
YOU GUYS ARE GOOD?

17:28.848 --> 17:30.916
HEY, CAN WE GO TO THE
"KILL BILL" SCREENING
AT THE STUDENT CENTER?

17:30.916 --> 17:31.984
AH, YEAH. CAN WE?

17:31.984 --> 17:33.285
YEAH, SURE.
SURE. HAVE FUN.

17:33.285 --> 17:34.954
REALLY? OKAY.
AWESOME. LET'S GO.

17:34.954 --> 17:37.289
OH, GRAB THE FRIES
AND THE KETCHUP.
OH. AAH!

17:37.289 --> 17:38.591
LET'S GO.
BYE, YOU GUYS.

17:38.591 --> 17:40.192
LOVE YOU.

17:41.260 --> 17:42.862
WE'VE GOT GOOD KIDS.

17:42.862 --> 17:44.196
YEAH, WE DO.

17:44.196 --> 17:46.966
I WISH THEY HAD LEFT THE FRIES.
THIS IS MY CHEAT DAY.

17:48.834 --> 17:50.169
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:50.169 --> 17:53.873
I'M TAKING A QUIZ
TO SEE WHAT KIND OF LOVER I AM.

17:53.873 --> 17:55.941
AND ALL SIGNS POINT TO...

17:57.042 --> 17:58.577
OOH.
THAT IS A GROWN-UP WORD.

17:58.577 --> 18:00.880
TEVIN:
BOOM! EAT FEATHER.

18:00.880 --> 18:01.981
I NEED A BREAK.

18:01.981 --> 18:04.216
MEG, PLEASE HELP ME
IN THE KITCHEN.

18:04.216 --> 18:05.050
OKAY.

18:05.050 --> 18:06.452
ADELE, TAG IN.

18:07.887 --> 18:10.423
LIFT ME UP.

18:10.423 --> 18:12.558
[ GRUNTS ]

18:12.558 --> 18:15.828
YOU HAVE GOT TO
GET TEVIN OUT OF HERE.

18:15.828 --> 18:16.562
WHAT? WHY?

18:16.562 --> 18:18.130
HE'S TAKING OVER
EVERYTHING.

18:18.130 --> 18:20.366
IT WAS FUN WHEN HE BURPED
THE FIRST 10 TIMES,

18:20.366 --> 18:23.869
BUT NOW THE WHOLE HOUSE SMELLS
LIKE WHITE CHEDDAR POPCORN.

18:23.869 --> 18:25.938
OH, MAN, BUT HE'S HAVING
SO MUCH WITH YOU GUYS.

18:25.938 --> 18:27.373
AND I'M ALWAYS
THE BAD GUY.

18:27.373 --> 18:30.042
THIS ONE'S ON YOU,
BUDDY.

18:30.042 --> 18:31.377
[ GROANS ]

18:36.549 --> 18:37.917
I'M OKAY.

18:40.853 --> 18:41.921
KATE.

18:41.921 --> 18:43.389
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,

18:43.389 --> 18:45.891
BUT I'VE GOT THIS CLICK
IN MY KNEE

18:45.891 --> 18:47.426
THAT REALLY ONLY BUGS ME
WHEN I'M PLAYING TENNIS.

18:47.426 --> 18:48.494
CAN YOU TAKE A LOOK
AT IT?

18:49.562 --> 18:51.597
MARCY, WHAT IS IT
YOU DO FOR A LIVING?

18:51.597 --> 18:53.999
UM, I'M AN I.T.
PROJECT MANAGER.

18:53.999 --> 18:55.267
UGH.

18:55.267 --> 18:58.871
WELL, I WOULDN'T ASK YOU
TO PROJECT-MANAGE MY I.T.

18:58.871 --> 19:00.039
AT A PARTY, YOU KNOW?

19:00.039 --> 19:01.106
SO, I DON'T THINK SO.

19:01.106 --> 19:02.942
AND, PLUS, STOP FLIRTING
WITH ME, OKAY?

19:02.942 --> 19:04.376
I'M TAKEN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:04.376 --> 19:07.580
OH. HI. JACKIE, I THOUGHT YOU
WERE PULLING THE CAR AROUND.

19:07.580 --> 19:08.914
I WAS,
BUT YOU HAVE THE KEYS.

19:08.914 --> 19:10.850
OH.

19:10.850 --> 19:12.918
PLUS, THERE'S SOMETHING
I WANT TO SAY TO HER.

19:12.918 --> 19:14.553
WHAT?

19:14.553 --> 19:17.223
MARCY, WHEN WE WERE
IN HIGH SCHOOL,

19:17.223 --> 19:19.458
YOU WERE REALLY MEAN TO ME,
AND SO I DECIDED --

19:19.458 --> 19:21.026
HONEY,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:21.026 --> 19:22.161
SORRY.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.229
I WANT TO DANCE.

19:23.229 --> 19:24.196
THIS IS OUR SONG.

19:24.196 --> 19:25.331
I DON'T KNOW THIS SONG.
SHH-SHH.

19:25.331 --> 19:27.166
JUST PUT YOUR HAND ON MY ASS
AND PRETEND.

19:27.166 --> 19:27.967
OH.

19:27.967 --> 19:29.435
WHY DID YOU DO THAT?

19:29.435 --> 19:30.936
BECAUSE MARCY'S A DONKEY

19:30.936 --> 19:33.873
AND I WANT TO DANCE
WITH THE COOL GIRL AT THE PARTY.

19:33.873 --> 19:36.942
OH! THANK YOU, KATE!

19:36.942 --> 19:38.444
OH!

19:38.444 --> 19:41.981
BERT: THERE ARE SO MANY STAGES
IN LIFE --

19:41.981 --> 19:44.583
KID, OLDER KID, GROWN-UP.

19:44.583 --> 19:47.319
EACH ONE IS SPECIAL.

19:49.488 --> 19:52.091
IT'S FUN TO LOOK BACK
ON THE PERSON YOU WERE...

19:55.995 --> 19:58.898
...AND REMEMBER
WHO YOU WANTED TO BE.

20:01.000 --> 20:02.968
BUT YOU HAVE TO
LOOK FORWARD, TOO,

20:02.968 --> 20:06.372
BECAUSE MOST OF THE TIME,
YOU DON'T EVEN REALIZE

20:06.372 --> 20:09.174
YOU'RE READY TO MOVE ON
TO THE NEXT CHAPTER

20:09.174 --> 20:11.110
UNTIL YOU'RE
ALREADY THERE.

20:11.110 --> 20:12.878
I GUESS WHAT I'M SAYING IS,

20:12.878 --> 20:16.315
I THINK YOU NEED TO FIND FRIENDS
YOUR OWN AGE.

20:16.315 --> 20:17.149
[ SCOFFS ]

20:17.149 --> 20:20.152
FINE. WHATEVER!

20:20.152 --> 20:21.320
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:21.320 --> 20:23.155
YOU SUCK AT BURPING.

20:25.391 --> 20:26.358
BARRY WHITE!

20:26.358 --> 20:27.860
WHAT A BABY.

20:28.928 --> 20:31.497
UGH. IT'S 9:15.

20:31.497 --> 20:34.433
I AM GONNA BE
USELESS TOMORROW.

20:34.433 --> 20:35.968
[ GROANS ]

20:41.073 --> 20:42.541
SHOULD WE WAKE THEM UP?

20:42.541 --> 20:43.876
OH, IT'S 2:00
IN THE AFTERNOON.

20:43.876 --> 20:45.277
I'M SURE THEY'VE GOTTEN
THEIR EIGHT HOURS.

20:45.277 --> 20:47.079
[ WHISTLES ]
GOOD MORNING!

20:47.079 --> 20:48.380
IS IT
TOMORROW NOW?

20:48.380 --> 20:50.049
TWO QUESTIONS.

20:50.049 --> 20:51.383
MAYBE MORE.

20:51.383 --> 20:53.052
HOW ARE YOU
STILL SLEEPING?

20:53.052 --> 20:54.920
AND WHY ARE YOU
WEARING OUR PAJAMAS?

20:54.920 --> 20:55.988
OH, LOUD!

20:55.988 --> 20:57.990
MEG, I TOLD YOU TO SLEEP
ON THE PULLOUT.

20:57.990 --> 20:59.558
WELL, IF IT MAKES YOU
FEEL ANY BETTER,

20:59.558 --> 21:02.127
WE DIDN'T DO MUCH SLEEPING,
AND WE DEFINITELY DIDN'T PULL --

21:02.127 --> 21:03.228
OKAY, OUT!

21:03.228 --> 21:04.997
OUT OF THE BED
SO WE CAN BURN THESE SHEETS.

21:04.997 --> 21:07.266
WHY AREN'T YOU MOVING?
WHY AREN'T THEY MOVING?

21:07.266 --> 21:09.068
LET ME PUT IT
THIS WAY.

21:09.068 --> 21:11.937
YOU SHOULD ONLY BE HALF MAD
AT US FOR WEARING YOUR PAJAMAS.

21:11.937 --> 21:13.539
OKAY. OKAY.
I'M OUT. I'M OUT.

21:13.539 --> 21:16.075
GET OUT!

21:16.075 --> 21:18.544
UM, THERE IS THE MATTER
OF OUR PAYMENT?

21:20.012 --> 21:21.847
NOT A GOOD TIME.
GOTCHA.

21:21.847 --> 21:23.248
WE'LL TALK
AFTER BREAKFAST.
